  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I remove the montage sound from video?",
  "response": "Removing montage sound or any undesired audio from a video can be done using several software tools. Here's a step-by-step guide using some popular options:\n\n### Using Adobe Premiere Pro:\n1. **Import the Video**: Open Premiere Pro and import your video by dragging it into the project panel.\n2. **Separate Audio from Video**:\n   - Drag the video to the timeline.\n   - Right-click on the video track in the timeline and select \"Unlink\". This separates the audio from the video.\n3. **Remove Audio**: Click on the audio track to select it and then press the 'Delete' key.\n4. **Export the Video**: After editing, go to 'File' > 'Export' > 'Media'. Choose your export settings and click 'Export'.\n\n### Using Final Cut Pro:\n1. **Import the Video**: Open Final Cut Pro, start a new project, and import your video.\n2. **Detach Audio**:\n   - Drag your video to the timeline.\n   - Right-click on the video clip and select \"Detach Audio\".\n3. **Delete Audio**: Select the audio track and press 'Delete'.\n4. **Export the Video**: Go to 'File' > 'Share' > 'Master File' to export the video.\n\n### Using iMovie (Mac):\n1. **Import Video**: Open iMovie and create a new project. Import your video file.\n2. **Detach Audio**:\n   - Drag your video to the timeline.\n   - Right-click the video clip and select \"Detach Audio\".\n3. **Remove Audio**: Select the audio track, then click 'Delete'.\n4. **Export the Video**: Click \u2018File\u2019 > \u2018Share\u2019 > \u2018File\u2019 to export the video.\n\n### Using DaVinci Resolve:\n1. **Import Video**: Open DaVinci Resolve and start a new project. Import your video.\n2. **Separate Audio**:\n   - Drag the video clip to the timeline.\n   - Right-click the video clip and select \u201cLink Clips\u201d to unlink the audio and video.\n3. **Delete Audio**: Select the audio track and delete it.\n4. **Export the Video**: Go to \u201cDeliver\u201d tab, set your export settings, and click \u201cAdd to Render Queue\u201d then \u201cStart Render\u201d.\n\n### Using VLC (Basic Audio Removal):\n1. **Open VLC**: Open VLC Media Player.\n2. **Convert/Save**:\n   - Go to \u2018Media\u2019 > \u2018Convert/Save\u2019.\n   - Add your video file.\n   - Click \u2018Convert/Save\u2019.\n3. **Settings**:\n   - Choose a profile.\n   - Click the \u2018Edit selected profile\u2019 button.\n   - Go to the \u2018Audio codec\u2019 tab and uncheck the \u2018Audio\u2019 box.\n4. **Convert**: Choose your destination and click \u2018Start\u2019.\n\nThese methods will help you remove or isolate the unwanted montage sound, allowing you to replace it or keep only the video content as needed.",
